The paper deals with the computational complexity of solving differential equations, which is a topic that falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of Lipschitz continuous and smooth functions suggests that numerical analysis (cs.NA) may also be relevant. The mention of PSPACE-hardness and the counting hierarchy suggests that the paper may also be related to complexity theory (cs.DS) and computational complexity in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of polynomial-time computable functions suggests that computational geometry (cs.CG) may also be relevant.
